Leading with Purpose

“Leading with Purpose” isn’t just a phrase — it’s how I show up. As a South Asian woman navigating predominantly white institutions and high-performance environments, I’ve learned that leadership isn’t always loud, but it’s always felt. My purpose stems from moments when I wasn’t included — and decided I’d never let others feel the same. From leading Desi Chargers to launching inclusive events through OGISL, I create systems where people feel seen, heard, and safe to show up fully. I’ve mentored peers, challenged traditions, and stepped into leadership roles not just for the title — but because I saw the impact of unspoken representation. I lead through empathy, curiosity, and intentional listening, believing that the best leaders don’t create followers, they empower more leaders. To lead with purpose is to build bridges — across cultures, across stories, and into a more human future.

About Me

I'm Mahek Bhagchandani — an Indian woman, lifelong learner, and passionate builder of inclusive communities. I’m currently pursuing a Master’s in Industrial and Organizational Psychology at the University of New Haven, where I’ve not only honed my academic knowledge in leadership, training, and HR systems, but also led real-world change across campus. Whether I’m founding Desi Chargers to give cultural identity a voice, mentoring new graduate assistants, or creating programming that bridges the gap for international students, I operate from a place of deep empathy and impact. My leadership style is bold, curious, and grounded in the belief that systems should support people — not the other way around. Since 2019, my story has been one of transition, trust, and transformation. Through research, relationships, and relentless effort, I aim to humanize workplaces, amplify underrepresented voices, and leave every space better than I found it.

Bachelor's Journey

Academic Excellence I graduated summa cum laude with a 3.81 GPA and earned Dean’s List honors four times during my Psychology degree. I was inducted into Psi Chi, the International Honor Society in Psychology, which recognized both my academic merit and research interest.

Debate Leadership My time in the debate club taught me how to lead under pressure and speak with impact. As Vice President and Social Media Head, I designed campaigns that attracted dozens of new members. I represented our university in the state tournament and the FIFA-hosted academic league, advocating for equity, ethics, and human behavior.

Cultural Impact I co-founded the South Asian Club because I saw how many South Asian students felt disconnected. I wanted to build more than events — I wanted to create cultural belonging. From Holi to film nights, we built a vibrant platform for sharing our stories.

Master's Journey

Founder and President – Desi Chargers Desi Chargers wasn’t just a dance team — it was a response to invisibility. I founded the group because I wanted graduate students from South Asian backgrounds to have a place to feel proud, expressive, and visible. We practiced in common rooms, performed at campus showcases, and ended up winning iFest 2025. Our team grew from 4 to 20 dancers and became a symbol of joy, community, and power. I led rehearsals, managed our executive board, and mentored our dancers across different cultures and skill levels.

Graduate Assistant – OGISL Hired in my very first semester, I’ve supported onboarding for 500+ graduate students, created training guides for new hires, and planned major university events. From Winter Ball to Disney Spring Break trips, I’ve worked behind the scenes on logistics, inclusive planning, and student engagement. I co-led team onboarding, collaborated across departments, and reimagined how students transition into grad life.

SHRM Head of Relations & Summer HR Intern Through SHRM, I coordinated HR guest speaker panels, hosted workshops on job readiness, and helped grow our student network. As a summer intern with OGISL, I’m focused on developing leadership training using psychological safety, peer feedback loops, and engagement models. I’ve also supported HR outreach strategy for international students.

Research & Innovation I designed a research study on leadership styles and job satisfaction using MLQ and JSS. I also conceptualized ThriveLocal, a platform to help relocated professionals connect with local businesses. I created the pitch, prototype, and brand story. Both projects allowed me to blend psychology, consulting, and strategy in real time.
